'3-Nitroaniline', also known as 'meta'-nitroaniline and m-nitroaniline, is non-
volatile stable solid commonly used as a raw material for dyes. 3-Nitroaniline
is an aniline carrying a nitro functional group in position 3. It is stable in
neutral, acidic or alkaline solutions and is classified as "not readily
biodegradable" with "low bioaccumulation potential" [http://72.14.253.104/searc-
h?q=cache:g1SWUzuysukJ:www.inchem.org/documents/sids/sids/99092.pdf+M-
nitroaniline&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=1&gl=au&client=firefox-a].

It is used as a chemical intermediate for azo coupling component 17 and the dyes
disperse yellow 5 and acid blue 29. The chemical is changed to other substances
(dyestuffs and m-nitrophenol) during the dyeing process.
